cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.THEORY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with logical properties of graphs generated by higher-order pushdown systems and ground tree rewriting systems. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses pushdown systems and their extensions. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper deals with stack trees, which are commonly used in programming languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper introduces a new class of graphs and discusses their properties. 
- cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with decidability properties of graphs generated by higher-order pushdown systems and ground tree rewriting systems.
